Razgulay, Mechel, Polymetal, Evraz: Russian Equity Preview

-- B y   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a
-- 
2011-10-11T20:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-11/razgulay-mechel-polymetal-evraz-russian-equity-preview.html
The following companies may be
active in Russian trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses and
share prices are from the previous close, unless noted
otherwise.  The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  fell 1.2 percent to 1,364.06.  Razgulay Group (GRAZ)  :  Russia ’s government may tax grain
exports once they reach 23 million to 24 million metric tons for
the marketing year, First Deputy Prime Minister Viktor Zubkov
said. Razgulay, a grain and sugar producer, was unchanged at
30.89 rubles in Moscow.  OAO  Mechel (MTLR)  , Russia’s largest maker of coal for
steelmakers, reduced its 2011 coal output forecast by about 10
percent after suspending two mines. Shares in Mechel fell 2.2
percent to 333.20 rubles in Moscow.  OAO Polymetal (PMTL RX): Russian gold producers Polymetal
International Plc and Polyus Gold International Ltd. may qualify
for inclusion in the U.K.’s benchmark stock index in December,
 Alfa Bank  said. Polymetal fell 1.4 percent to 475.30 rubles in
Moscow.  Evraz Group SA (EVR)  : Evraz Group plans to publish
earnings for the first half of the year on Oct. 12. The company,
Russia’s largest steelmaker by output, fell 1.1 percent to
$15.66 in  London .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marina Sysoyeva in Moscow at 
